ASSIGNMENT 3, Ambrosius Patrick Tjahjono

this program will let terminal to communicate with each other by speciying the ports used in this format "lets-talk 'my port number/source' localhost 'destination port number'"

required lib/commandline in terminal:
sudo apt-get install libreadline-dev

SOURCE WEB:
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/socket-programming-cc/
http://beej.us/guide/bgnet/pdf/bgnet_usl_c_1.pdf
https://linux.die.net/man/3/inet_ntoa
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/socket-programming-cc/
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/mutex-lock-for-linux-thread-synchronization/
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/condition-wait-signal-multi-threading/
